cpu-power-manager (1.0.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Dashboard & Monitoring:
    - System Overview redesign — 4-column homogeneous grid ensures metric cards never overlap;
      text no longer spills into adjacent cells
    - Intel RAPL power draw — live watts reading via two-sample energy delta from
      /sys/class/powercap/intel-rapl
    - Battery status card — charge %, AC/battery detection, live power draw, and charge status
      string
    - Fan speed — live RPM from hwmon drivers displayed alongside CPU info
    - Per-core temperatures — reads coretemp hwmon labels (Core 0, Core 1 …) and displays next
      to each core row
    - Per-core CPU usage bars — LevelBar widget per core updated every second
    - P-core / E-core labels — Intel 12th gen+ hybrid CPUs now correctly label [P] and [E] cores

  * Control:
    - Frequency sliders — min/max Scale widgets in the Control tab with a single Apply button
    - AC / Battery auto-profile switching — detects power source change every second and applies
      the configured profile automatically

  * Settings:
    - Display Size — Small / Normal / Large / X-Large dropdown; scales the entire UI instantly,
      persisted across restarts
    - Launch at Login — writes/removes ~/.config/autostart/cpu-power-manager.desktop
    - Minimize to Tray on Close — hides window instead of quitting
    - Auto-Apply Profile on Startup — restores last used profile on launch
    - Critical Temperature Notification — desktop notification toggle with configurable °C
      threshold
    - Custom profile creation — name, governor, and turbo setting saved to config; persists
      across restarts

  * System Tray:
    - StatusNotifierItem tray icon via pure-Rust zbus — no libdbus-1-dev C headers required
    - Show/Hide Window and Quit menu entries
    - Fails gracefully when no DBus session bus is present

  * UI & Design:
    - Full Dracula colour palette — all backgrounds, text, accents, status colours, graph,
      scrollbars, and buttons now use canonical Dracula colours (#282a36, #bd93f9, #50fa7b,
      #f1fa8c, #ff5555, #8be9fd, etc.)
    - macOS-style circular traffic-light buttons — replaced GTK Button widgets (which cannot be
      forced circular via CSS) with Cairo-drawn DrawingArea dots; red/yellow/green 13 px circles
      with hover dimming
    - CPU usage graph recoloured to Dracula purple (#bd93f9) fill and line
    - App icon — lightning bolt SVG registered in the icon theme at runtime; no system
      installation required for the icon to appear
    - About dialog — logo loads from embedded SVG bytes (always visible); website updated to
      www.jegly.xyz

  * Bug Fixes:
    - "Expected a valid color" CSS parse error — removed unsupported box-shadow: inset from
      drawingarea block
    - "Failed to read available governors" — governor lookup now falls back to cpu0, then to a
      hardcoded Intel pstate list, instead of bailing on first failure
    - "Failed to reset min frequency for core N" — E-core frequency writes are now soft errors
      (debug log only); profile apply no longer aborts on hybrid CPUs
    - Per-core panel empty — get_core_status() uses unwrap_or for all sysfs reads;
      get_all_core_status() uses filter_map so one failing core doesn't block the rest
    - Fan Speed / CPU Info overlap — fan speed card (grid index 7) was being placed at the same
      cell as the CPU info card; fixed by folding fan speed into the CPU info card

  * Configuration:
    New fields in ~/.config/cpu-power-manager/config.toml:
      minimize_to_tray = false
      auto_apply_on_startup = false
      last_profile = ""
      critical_temp_notify = true
      ui_scale = "normal" # small | normal | large | xlarge
    Existing configs are forward-compatible — all new fields have defaults and are optional.

  * Known Limitations:
    - E-core frequencies display as 0 MHz on Intel 12th gen+ — expected behaviour; E-cores share
      a policy group and don't expose individual scaling_cur_freq files
    - System tray requires sudo -E (not plain sudo) to preserve DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS

